<recipe>
<title>
Lemon Coconut Cookies
</title>
<details>

</details>
<ingredients>
2 c . all-purpose flour
1 T . cornstarch
1/2 tsp . baking soda
1/2 tsp . kosher salt
1 c . granulated sugar
1 large egg
1 egg yolk
1/3 c . coconut oil melted
1/2 tsp . vanilla extract
1/4 c . freshly squeezed lemon juice
2 tsp . freshly grated lemon zest/rind
1/2 c . shredded sweetened coconut
1/4 c . powdered sugar
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Preheat oven to 350 F. Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper or silicone baking mats.
In a medium bowl, whisk flour, corn starch, baking soda, and salt together. Set aside.
In a large bowl, beat together granulated sugar, egg, and egg yolk until well-combined.
Add melted coconut oil and vanilla; stir well to combine.
Stir in lemon juice and lemon zest.
Stir in flour mixture, and mix until just incorporated.
Add coconut, and stir until just combined.
Using a medium cookie scoop (1 Â½ tablespoons), scoop dough.
Roll dough balls in powdered sugar, and then place dough balls on prepared baking sheets about 2 inches apart.
Bake for 8-10 minutes, or until middle is set and edges are very light golden brown.
</instructions>
</recipe>
